Now how many marathons
a week are you

00:01:47.690 --> 00:01:49.070 align:middle line:90%
running to burn it all off?

00:01:49.070 --> 00:01:50.510 align:middle line:90%
Two?

00:01:50.510 --> 00:01:51.940 align:middle line:90%
Three?

00:01:51.940 --> 00:01:53.455 align:middle line:90%
None?

00:01:53.455 --> 00:01:55.080 align:middle line:84%
So what happens is,
of course, the body

00:01:55.080 --> 00:01:58.320 align:middle line:84%
is producing all this insulin
to metabolize the sugar.

00:01:58.320 --> 00:02:01.140 align:middle line:84%
And of course, all
of this insulin

00:02:01.140 --> 00:02:02.890 align:middle line:84%
is causing a problem
for the cells.

00:02:02.890 --> 00:02:04.712 align:middle line:84%
The cells become
resistant to the insulin,

00:02:04.712 --> 00:02:07.170 align:middle line:84%
and then we move into this very
common condition now called

00:02:07.170 --> 00:02:08.103 align:middle line:90%
type 2 diabetes.

00:02:08.103 --> 00:02:10.020 align:middle line:84%
Let's not forget, there
are millions of people

00:02:10.020 --> 00:02:12.960 align:middle line:84%
out there in the threshold
of going into type 2 syndrome

00:02:12.960 --> 00:02:15.780 align:middle line:84%
x, what we call insulin
resistance, dry mouth, peeing

00:02:15.780 --> 00:02:17.190 align:middle line:90%
a little and often.

00:02:17.190 --> 00:02:18.900 align:middle line:84%
These types of, you
know, tunnel vision,

00:02:18.900 --> 00:02:22.230 align:middle line:84%
blurry vision, this
type of thing happening.

00:02:22.230 --> 00:02:24.600 align:middle line:84%
Having the desire
to get in your car

00:02:24.600 --> 00:02:26.640 align:middle line:84%
