So on top of diabetes, we
now get loads of problems

00:02:34.980 --> 00:02:38.670 align:middle line:84%
with yeast, fungi,
candida breaking out.

00:02:38.670 --> 00:02:42.390 align:middle line:84%
So the answer is with diabetes
is, again, diet and lifestyle.

00:02:42.390 --> 00:02:45.120 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the sheer idiocy
of just giving type

00:02:45.120 --> 00:02:47.160 align:middle line:84%
2 diabetics more
insulin, more of what

00:02:47.160 --> 00:02:51.425 align:middle line:84%
they're resistant to
to start with is dumb.

00:02:51.425 --> 00:02:52.800 align:middle line:84%
And what we should
be doing again

00:02:52.800 --> 00:02:54.870 align:middle line:84%
is, and they are
starting to do this,

00:02:54.870 --> 00:02:56.580 align:middle line:84%
is to concentrate
on diet, put them

00:02:56.580 --> 00:02:59.220 align:middle line:84%
on these anti-candida diets
to strip the glucose out

00:02:59.220 --> 00:03:00.150 align:middle line:90%
of the diet.

00:03:00.150 --> 00:03:02.200 align:middle line:90%
Exercise is very important.

00:03:02.200 --> 00:03:04.380 align:middle line:84%
Remember, type 2 diabetes
is when the cells

00:03:04.380 --> 00:03:05.730 align:middle line:90%
are resistant to insulin.

00:03:05.730 --> 00:03:07.230 align:middle line:84%
So now what we've
got to do is we've

00:03:07.230 --> 00:03:10.020 align:middle line:84%
got to be able to free
up the insulin pathway.

00:03:10.020 --> 00:03:12.660 align:middle line:84%
And the way we do that
is we exercise that body

00:03:12.660 --> 00:03:14.070 align:middle line:90%
so the cells burn the energy.

00:03:14.070 --> 00:03:16.530 align:middle line:84%
And therefore, they
require more sugar,

00:03:16.530 --> 00:03:18.300 align:middle line:84%
so that frees up
that whole problem.

00:03:18.300 --> 00:03:21.970 align:middle line:84%
And in early type 2 diabetes,
diet supplementation,

00:03:21.970 --> 00:03:23.970 align:middle line:84%
we use chromium, vanadium,
number of supplements

00:03:23.970 --> 00:03:24.810 align:middle line:90%
to do that.

00:03:24.810 --> 00:03:27.060 align:middle line:84%
And also the
straightforward dietary

00:03:27.060 --> 00:03:29.610 align:middle line:84%
changes that we
discuss in the books.

00:03:29.610 --> 00:03:32.260 align:middle line:84%
This should be part of
every household's education.

00:03:32.260 --> 00:03:35.250 align:middle line:84%
But you see, diabetes
is still the preserve

00:03:35.250 --> 00:03:36.493 align:middle line:90%
of the medical doctor.

00:03:36.493 --> 00:03:38.160 align:middle line:84%
And so what we're not
doing is we're not

00:03:38.160 --> 00:03:40.170 align:middle line:84%
educating the
public enough to be

00:03:40.170 --> 00:03:41.400 align:middle line:90%
able to avoid these problems.

00:03:41.400 --> 00:03:43.320 align:middle line:84%
Believe it or not,
they're willing to listen

00:03:43.320 --> 00:03:44.403 align:middle line:90%
once they start suffering.

00:03:44.403 --> 00:03:46.362 align:middle line:84%
But the big problem is
we've got lots of people

00:03:46.362 --> 00:03:49.110 align:middle line:84%
out there living the life of
Riley, having a great life,

00:03:49.110 --> 00:03:49.950 align:middle line:90%
and that's good.

00:03:49.950 --> 00:03:52.570 align:middle line:84%
But they're doing
wrong by themselves.

00:03:52.570 --> 00:03:56.010 align:middle line:84%
And so nature's going to
sharpen her sword for them.

00:03:56.010 --> 00:03:58.320 align:middle line:84%
If I was diagnosed
with diabetes type 2,

00:03:58.320 --> 00:04:01.457 align:middle line:84%
the very first thing
that I would think about

00:04:01.457 --> 00:04:03.540 align:middle line:84%
would I'd first of all go
back and read my chapter

00:04:03.540 --> 00:04:08.096 align:middle line:84%
on diabetes, which discusses--
and this is what they found.

00:04:08.096 --> 00:04:11.910 align:middle line:84%
That we strip the
refined high glycemic

00:04:11.910 --> 00:04:14.280 align:middle line:84%
carbohydrates out of
the diet first thing.

00:04:14.280 --> 00:04:16.570 align:middle line:84%
Because what's happening is
that if you have diabetes,

00:04:16.570 --> 00:04:18.237 align:middle line:84%
you have a condition
where the cells are

00:04:18.237 --> 00:04:19.350 align:middle line:90%
resistant to the insulin.

00:04:19.350 --> 00:04:21.907 align:middle line:84%
So simply by giving the
body more sugar to process

00:04:21.907 --> 00:04:23.490 align:middle line:84%
is just going to
compound the problem,

00:04:23.490 --> 00:04:26.280 align:middle line:84%
requiring more insulin
to be put into the body.

00:04:26.280 --> 00:04:28.950 align:middle line:84%
So the studies that we've looked
at are pretty unequivocal.

00:04:28.950 --> 00:04:31.560 align:middle line:84%
First thing to do if
you have type 2 diabetes

00:04:31.560 --> 00:04:34.620 align:middle line:84%
is to change your
diet, to remove

00:04:34.620 --> 00:04:36.750 align:middle line:84%
a lot of these high
sugar foods, and to start

00:04:36.750 --> 00:04:40.830 align:middle line:84%
to put the emphasis on a lot
of the raw natural whole foods,

00:04:40.830 --> 00:04:42.420 align:middle line:90%
lots of greens.

00:04:42.420 --> 00:04:44.530 align:middle line:84%
Greens are great because
they contain chlorophyll,

00:04:44.530 --> 00:04:47.460 align:middle line:84%
which increases the amount of
oxygen uptake in the blood.

00:04:47.460 --> 00:04:50.220 align:middle line:84%
Converts the hemoglobin, which
is very useful for the body.

00:04:50.220 --> 00:04:52.200 align:middle line:84%
The next thing I'd
do is exercise.

00:04:52.200 --> 00:04:54.172 align:middle line:90%
And I'd start off by--

00:04:54.172 --> 00:04:56.130 align:middle line:84%
a lot of people think
that walking is exercise.

00:04:56.130 --> 00:04:59.040 align:middle line:84%
Walking is not exercise from the
cardiovascular point of view,

00:04:59.040 --> 00:05:01.500 align:middle line:84%
because it's not putting
the cardiovascular system

00:05:01.500 --> 00:05:03.240 align:middle line:84%
under any kind of
significant strain.

00:05:03.240 --> 00:05:05.770 align:middle line:84%
What we need to do is get
slightly out of breath.

00:05:05.770 --> 00:05:07.300 align:middle line:90%
So I'd be doing stair climbing.

00:05:07.300 --> 00:05:10.050 align:middle line:84%
I'd be using those horrendous
machines in the gym.

00:05:10.050 --> 00:05:12.270 align:middle line:84%
They never go anywhere,
have you noticed that?

00:05:12.270 --> 00:05:15.030 align:middle line:84%
And just exercising,
getting out of breath.

00:05:15.030 --> 00:05:17.220 align:middle line:84%
When I lived in Santa
Monica, California,

00:05:17.220 --> 00:05:20.910 align:middle line:84%
they had these stairways,
200 steps going up

00:05:20.910 --> 00:05:22.210 align:middle line:90%
the side of the hill.

00:05:22.210 --> 00:05:24.690 align:middle line:84%
And often when I'd go down
there and run up them myself,

00:05:24.690 --> 00:05:27.510 align:middle line:84%
there was diabetics there who
were exercising specifically

00:05:27.510 --> 00:05:29.130 align:middle line:90%
for their condition.

00:05:29.130 --> 00:05:32.030 align:middle line:84%
And lastly, the supplementation,
minerals, antioxidants,

00:05:32.030 --> 00:05:34.655 align:middle line:84%
and things like vanadium and
chromium supplements, chromium

00:05:34.655 --> 00:05:37.260 align:middle line:84%
picolinate have
been shown to help

00:05:37.260 --> 00:05:39.030 align:middle line:90%
cells recognize the insulin.

00:05:39.030 --> 00:05:41.930 align:middle line:84%
And generally in the
early stages of type 2,

00:05:41.930 --> 00:05:44.940 align:middle line:84%
there is every chance that
people can come out of it.

00:05:44.940 --> 00:05:47.080 align:middle line:84%
As the disease
progresses, in fact

00:05:47.080 --> 00:05:49.950 align:middle line:84%
the more the disease progresses,
the uglier your options become.

00:05:49.950 --> 00:05:54.060 align:middle line:84%
So it's very important to get
into diabetes nice and early

00:05:54.060 --> 00:05:55.560 align:middle line:90%
and to not fool around.

00:05:55.560 --> 00:05:57.540 align:middle line:84%
Just get the diet
sorted out, exercise,

00:05:57.540 --> 00:06:01.740 align:middle line:84%
